page.title: 14THE DIBBINSDALE WOODS
page.content: In our block we have a varity of wildlife-woodlands,the{Dibbin} stream,farmland and a golf course. The{Dibbin}is a stream which runs through{Dibbinsdale Woods}.There is a varity of wildlife in the woods including plants,toadstools,animals and birds. The{Dibbin}area is looked after by wardens.They make sure that no-one harms the wildlife.They are helped by people on a{Youth Opportunities} {Scheme.}These people have made a nature trail so that others can enjoy the countryside without spoiling it. The elm tree in our area is endangered because of a beetle called the{Dutch Elm Beetle.}The beetle lays its eggs inside tunnels. It also carries a fungus which clogs up the sap and the tree dies.
